<item>
            <title>[LU-209] &quot;make rpms&quot; should use lbuild script</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-209</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;We were discussing today that Brian was working on the &quot;lbuild&quot; script so that it could be run by mortals, without any command-line options.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It would also be useful if &quot;make rpms&quot; can also build RPMs from the current source tree.  AFAIK, lbuild can use a pre-specified kernel source tree, which can be derived from the &quot;configure --with-linux&quot; data for &quot;make rpms&quot;, and hopefully other required options can be similarly derived.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
